  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   In Guangdong Province, the Beijiang River was at 14.72 meters, about 4.22 meters above the danger mark, late yesterday,
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   and the flood peak on the Xijiang River was reached today.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Flooding in Hunan Province's Changsha from the Xiangjiang River has affected more the 300,000 residents
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   and closed more the 400 factories and 5,000 shops.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Late last night, the flood peak passed through Jiangxi Province's capital, Nanchang.
